The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Aug. 4: Reservations for Scheduled Caste and Scheduled Tribe in Parliament and Assemblies have been extended by 10 years.           
	The Constitution had originally provided the reservation for 10 years but it has been stretched to 70 years with this latest extension. The bill also extends the nomination of Anglo Indians.                   
	 Mumbai: Indian Airlines Flight IC 685 from Ahmedabad to Mumbai made an emergency landing at the airport here on Tuesday evening after reporting a hydraulic failure. Full emergency was declared at the airport at 8.30pm. The flight landed successfully at 8.49pm with all 137 passengers safe. Emergency was withdrawn at 8.57pm.                   
	 New Delhi: The Supreme Court on Tuesday stayed a Bombay High Court order asking the Maharashtra government to submit the Ram Pradhan committee report on the lapses in the states response to the Mumbai attacks. The high court had asked for a copy of the report while hearing a PIL alleging the lapses.                   
	 New Delhi: The BJP leadership has shifted the Chintan Baithak organised to analyse the defeat in the general elections and draw the future course of action. The event has been shifted from Mumbai to Shimla because of the Mumbai rains. The three-day session will start on August 17.                  
	 Bangalore (PTI): Three children, aged between three and seven, were charred to death when their hut caught fire in Bangalore on Tuesday. Their hut was bolted from outside, police said. The cause of the fire is not yet known. A search is on for the parents.                  
	 Mumbai: Bhupen Hazarika underwent a successful bypass surgery at Mumbais Kolkilaben Dhirubhai Ambani Hospital on Tuesday and has been put on ventilator. Hazarikas companion, film director Kalpana Lajmi said it was normal procedure to put a patient on ventilator after a bypass surgery.                                                                                                                           
